Thus the heating element circuit is closed, the iron heats 
up. The bimetal strip which is also heated, bends upwards 
and the   insulated   block pushes the   strip A,   thereby, 
separating the silver contacts and the heating element 
circuit opens. 
When the iron cools down, the bimetallic strip also cools 
and comes back to   the straight position. The downward 
movement   of   the insulated blockallows silver contact strip 
A to come   in contact with the   silver contact strip B: 
thereby the circuit is closed and the iron heats up. 
