anddry irons. Asteamironhas asmall reservoir   mounted 
above the heating element. Acontrol valve onthis allows 
the water to drip slowly into recesses in the sole-plate. 
Acheckvalve keeps the water from going back upintothe 
tank. When the water hits the hot position of the sole- 
plate, itis convertedto steam and goes out through holes 
inthe bottom of the sole-plate. Fig 4 shows a diagram of 
