 Features of the food mixer 
 The   motor   housing   differs   widely   depending   on   the 
manufacturer. Special care to be taken for vibration-free 
running.   Safety features such as overloadtrip, jar mounting 
lock (fixing) and proper lid closing are included in the 
appliances. 
An AC universal motor is housed in the base. The jar 
contains the   cutting   knives which   is the   heart of the 
blending action. Fig   2 shows a schematic diagram of a 
typical mixer. 
Afood mixer power rating ranges from 100 to 750 watts. 
The revolution of the food mixer is 3000 to 14000 revolutions 
per min. The desired speed is selected on the control 
switch. 
