*   explain Iron (No -   load) losses and copper (load) losses in transformer. 
 Losses 
 There are two type of losses occured in the transformer 
such as iron (core) loss (Hysterisis   + eddy current) and 
copper (Ohmic) or load loss 
Iron (or) No-load losses: The no load losses consist of 
two components i.e hysteresis and eddy current loss. The 
hysteresis loss due to the cyclic variation of the magnetic 
flux in the ferrous metal. 
The eddy current occurs because of the changing flux in 
the core, (according to Lenz''s law) inducing avoltage inthe 
core. As a result, circulating eddy currents set up in the 
core with subsequent I°R loss. This is also calledas iron 
loss (or) coreloss (or) constantlosses. 
As the   core flux   in   a transformer   remains   practically 
constant at all loads, the core-loss is also constant at all 
loads.   This is also known as no-load losses. 
